  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 7:10",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Chronicles 7:10",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "On the three and twentieth day of the seventh month, he sent the people away — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "They kept the feast of the dedication of the altar seven days, from the second to the ninth; the tenth day was the day of atonement, when they were to afflict their souls for sin, and that was not unseasonable in the midst of their rejoicings: then on the fifteenth began the feast of tabernacles, which continued to the twenty-second, and thus they continued to be employed in sacred services, and did not part till the twenty-third. We ought never to grudge the time that we spend in the worship of God, and in communion with him, nor think it long, or grow weary of it. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Glad and merry in heart for the goodness, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "&c. — That is, according to the Targum, “for the goodness of the Lord shown unto ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "David, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "in opening the doors of the sanctuary; and unto ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Solomon, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "whose prayer God had accepted, and had honoured with his presence in the house which he had built; and unto ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "his people Israel, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "in his acceptance of their sacrifices, and sending down fire from heaven to consume them.”",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
